Silicon anode batteries represent a next‑generation lithium‑ion technology in which silicon, either as a pure anode or in hybrid form with graphite, replaces the conventional graphite‑only anode. Silicon can store up to ten times more lithium ions by weight, translating into up to 30 % higher gravimetric energy density for full cells. This enables longer discharge periods, higher specific power, and a smaller footprint-attributes that are critically important for both grid‑scale storage and electric‑vehicle applications.
